Source: greyfix
Section: mail
Priority: extra
Maintainer: Chris Smith <chris@cs278.org>
Build-Depends: cdbs, debhelper (>= 5), autotools-dev, libdb4.4-dev | libdb4.5-dev | libdb4.6-dev | libdb4.7-dev
Standards-Version: 3.7.2

Package: greyfix
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, adduser
Recommends: postfix (>= 2.1)
Description: Greyfix is the greylisting policy daemon for Postfix.
  Greyfix is the greylisting policy daemon for Postfix written by
  Kim Minh Kaplan.  Greylisting is an anti spam technique described by
  Evan Harris.  Postfix is a popular mail transport agent developped by
  Wietse Zweitze Venema.  Greyfix uses Postfix policy mechanism to
  enable greylisting with Postfix.
